org.osgeo.mapguide

Class MgServerAdmin

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.osgeo.mapguide.MgObject
      • org.osgeo.mapguide.MgDisposable
        • org.osgeo.mapguide.MgGuardDisposable
          • org.osgeo.mapguide.MgServerAdmin

  • public class MgServerAdmin
extends MgGuardDisposable
    This class contains methods to allow MapGuide clients to perform administration related operations: - Server Configuration - Logging - Online/Offline - Server Health

      • getLog

        public MgByteReader getLog(java.lang.String log,
                           MgDateTime fromDate,
                           MgDateTime toDate)
        (NOTE: This API is not officially supported and may be subject to removal in a future release without warning. Use with caution.) Gets the contents of the specified log between two dates. A maximum 24 hour period is allowed to be retrieved. This will use the current file name convention for the log so if the filename was changed it will be unable to find entries located previous files.
        Parameters:
        log - The log to retrieve. (AccessLog, AdminLog, AuthenticationLog, ErrorLog, MapLayerAccessLog, SessionLog, TraceLog)
        fromDate - Date and time to start pulling entries from
        toDate - Last date and time to pull entries for
        Returns:
        The log contents in a ByteReader.
        Throws:
        MgException - with code MgConnectionNotOpenException
        MgException - with code MgInvalidLogTypeException
        MgException - with code MgNullReferenceException
        MgException - with code MgInvalidArgumentException
        MgException - with code MgOutOfMemoryException
